# Plan: Live Router Metrics Dashboard

**Feature**: `.github/ROADMAP.md` line 7
**Priority**: 🔴 P1 | **Effort**: ⭐⭐⭐⭐
**Owner**: orchestratore | **Status**: ✅ Complete

Historical note: implemented and merged in Phase 1. Keep this file as feature record; do not use it as the current source of backlog truth.

---

## Objective

Implement **real-time TUI (Text UI) metrics dashboard** for router health monitoring.

Entry point: `python .github/router.py --dashboard`

Output: Interactive terminal UI showing:
- Confidence trend (rolling avg of last N queries)
- Scenario usage heatmap
- Agent overlap indicators
- Dead zones (unmatched queries)
- Exit codes and error rates

---

## Success Criteria

- [ ] TUI framework integrated (rich library, no external bloat)
- [ ] Metrics collected from `router.py --stats`
- [ ] Real-time refresh < 500ms (terminal I/O)
- [ ] Graceful degradation on non-TTY
- [ ] Test coverage > 85%
- [ ] Documentation in README

---

## Scope & Non-Scope

### In Scope
- CLI flag `--dashboard` in router.py
- Real-time metric collection from interventions.db
- Text-based UI (curses/rich)
- Export metrics to JSON (piping)

### Out of Scope
- Web-based dashboard
- Persistent metric storage (beyond existing interventions.db)
- Alert notifications (Slack, email)
- Performance optimization tier 2 (post-MVP)

---

## Design

### Architecture

```
router.py --dashboard
    ↓
RouterMetricsCollector (new class)
    ├─ confidence_trend()        → last 50 queries
    ├─ scenario_usage_heatmap()  → scenario frequency
    ├─ agent_overlap()           → competing agents
    ├─ dead_zones()              → unmatched patterns
    ├─ error_rate()              → fail % recent
    └─ refresh_interval (500ms)
    ↓
DashboardUI (curses/rich)
    ├─ Top panel: real-time metrics
    ├─ Middle: histogram scenarios
    ├─ Bottom: status + controls
    └─ Keyboard: 'q' quit, 'r' refresh, 'e' export
```

### File Changes

**New files**:
- `rgen/metrics_collector.py` — RouterMetricsCollector class
- `rgen/dashboard_ui.py` — DashboardUI class (TUI)
- `tests/test_dashboard_ui.py` — TUI unit tests
- `tests/test_metrics_collector.py` — metrics unit tests

**Modified files**:
- `core/router.py` — add `--dashboard` flag + main loop
- `tests/test_cli.py` — integration test for dashboard

### Dependencies

```diff
+ rich >= 13.0  (for TUI rendering, safe + lightweight)
```

(Avoid curses → platform-specific complexity)

